{"title_page": "Chaophraya Surasak", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                           = Chaophraya Surasak\n| official_name                  = City of Chaophraya Surasak<br>{{lang|th|\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e19\u0e04\u0e23\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c}}\n| native_name                    = {{lang|th|\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c}}\n| nickname                       = \n| translit_lang1                 = \n| translit_lang1_type1           = \n| translit_lang1_info1           =  \n| settlement_type                = [[List of municipalities in Thailand|City Municipality]]\n| motto                          =\n| image_skyline                  = \n| imagesize                      =\n| image_caption                  = \n| image_flag                     =\n| image_seal                     = {{#property:p158}}\n| image_shield                   =\n| image_map                      = \n| map_caption                    = \n| mapsize                        = \n| pushpin_map                    = Thailand Bay of Bangkok#Thailand\n| pushpin_label                  = <small>Chaophraya Surasak</small>\n| pushpin_label_position         = right\n| pushpin_map_caption            = Location in [[Bay of Bangkok]]##Location in [[Thailand]]\n| coordinates                    = {{coord|13|07|28|N|100|59|57|E|region:TH|display=inline}}\n| named_for                      = [[Chaophraya Surasakmontri]]\n| subdivision_type               = [[List of sovereign states|Country]] \n| subdivision_name               = [[Thailand]]\n| subdivision_type1              = [[Provinces of Thailand|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1              = [[Chonburi Province|Chonburi]]\n| subdivision_type2              = [[List of districts of Thailand|District]]\n| subdivision_name2              = [[Si Racha District|Si Racha]]\n| leader_title1                  = \n| leader_name1                   = \n| leader_title2                  =\n| leader_name2                   =\n| leader_title3                  =\n| leader_name3                   =\n| established_title              = Sanitation\n| established_date               = 12 December 1967\n| established_title1             = Subdistrict<br>municipality\n| established_date1              = 25 May 1999\n| established_title2             = City<br>municipality\n| established_date2              = 1 May 2013\n| seat_type                      =\n| seat                           =\n| government_footnotes           =\n| government_type                = \n| leader_party                   =\n| leader_title                   = Mayor\n| leader_name                    = Akom Panchalermchai\n| unit_pref                      = Metric\n| area_footnotes                 = \n| area_rank                      = 2nd\n| area_total_km2                 = 276.98\n| area_land_km2                  =\n| area_note                      = \n| elevation_footnotes            =\n| elevation_m                    =\n| population_footnotes           = <ref name=\"TDD\">{{cite web |url=http://stat.bora.dopa.go.th/stat/statnew/statTDD/ |title=\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e16\u0e34\u0e15\u0e34\u0e08\u0e33\u0e19\u0e27\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e01\u0e23\u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e08\u0e33\u0e1b\u0e35 \u0e1e.\u0e28.2562 |date=31 December 2019 |department=Registration Office Department of the Interior, Ministry of the Interior |language=Thai |trans-title=Statistics, population and house statistics for the year 2019 |access-date=10 March 2020 |postscript= , archiving is not necessary because DOPA provides data from 1993 to future years.}}</ref>\n| population_total               = 143,024\n| population_as_of               = 2019\n| population_rank                = 5th\n| population_density_km2         = 516\n| population_demonym             =\n| population_note                =\n| timezone1                      = [[UTC+07:00|ICT]]\n| utc_offset1                    = +7\n| postal_code_type               = [[Postal codes in Thailand|Postcode]]\n| postal_code                    = 20110\n| area_code_type                 = [[Telephone numbers in Thailand|Calling code]]\n| area_code                      = 038\n| website                        = {{URL|www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/}}\n| footnotes                      =\n}}\n\n'''Chaophraya Surasak''' is a city in [[Chonburi Province]], [[Thailand]].  It was established as a sanitary district in 1967. In 1999, all sanitary districts were upgraded to subdistrict municipalities (''[[Thesaban #Subdistrict-municipality|thesaban tambon]]''). In 2013 it was upgraded to a city municipality (''[[Thesaban#City-municipality|thesaban nakhon]]''). As of 2019, it has a population of 143,024.<ref name=\"TDD\"/> The city covers parts of five subdistricts (''[[tambon]]'') of [[Si Racha District]]. The city is named after [[Chaophraya Surasakmontri]].\n\n==Geography==\n===Location===\nChaophraya Surasak city municipality (''[[Thesaban#City-municipality|thesaban nakhon]]'') with a total area of 276.98 sq.km is located on the east coast of [[Gulf of Thailand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/554 |title=Location and physical characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> It is about 40 kilometers from [[Chonburi]] and 120 kilometers from [[Bangkok]]. Chaophraya Surasak borders to the '''north''': subdistricts (''tambon'') Bang Phra and Nong Kham, district (''amphoe'') Si Racha, province Chonburi, '''east''': subdistrict Khlon Kio, district Ban Bueng and subdistricts Khao Khan Song and Bo Win, district Si Racha, province Chonburi, '''south''': subdistrict Takhian Tia, [[Bang Lamung District|district Bang Lamung]], province Chonburi, '''west''': [[Laem Chabang]] city municipality and [[Si Racha]] town municipality (''[[Thesaban#Town-municipality|thesaban mueang]]''), district Si Racha, province Chonburi and the [[Bay of Bangkok]].\n\n===Topography===\nIn the east of the Chaophraya Surasak municipality is the [[Khao Khiao Massif|Khao Khiao]] mountain range. The foothills alternate with plains to the sea.<ref name=\"RESOURCE\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/560 |title=Resource characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Wildlife Sanctuary===\nThere is one wildlife sanctuary in Khao Khan Song subdistrict: [[Khao Khiao - Khao Chomphu Wildlife Sanctuary]], 145 sq.km (56 sq.mi.)\n\n===Climate===\nChaophraya Surasak city has a tropical savanna climate (K\u00f6ppen climate classification category Aw). Winters are dry and warm. Temperatures rise until May. Mansoon season runs from May through October, with heavy rain and somewhat cooler temperatures during the day, although nights remain warm. Weather station Laem Chabang, climate data from 1981-2010: The maximum temperature is 39.0 \u00b0C (102.2 \u00b0F) in January and the minimum temperature is 14.0 \u00b0C (57.2 \u00b0F) in December. The maximum average temperature is 33.3 \u00b0C (91.9 \u00b0F) in April and the minimum average temperature is 22.0 \u00b0C (71.6 \u00b0F) in December. Annual rainfall is 1,151 millimeter (45.3 inche) and in January was for 24 hour the rainfall 176.5 millimeter (7 inche).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.climate.tmd.go.th/content/file/75 |title=Climatological Data for the Period 1981-2010 |publisher=Thai Meteorological Department |page=20 |access-date=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Water resources===\nThere are three water reservoirs:\n* Huai Nong Kho, capacity 21,400,000 cub.m.\n* Huai Saphan, capacity 7,650,000 cub.m.\n* Huai Nong Klang Dong, capacity 3,840,00 cub.m.\nFurther there is natural stream Huai Lam, consisting of 20 natural places.<ref name=\"RESOURCE\"/>\n\n==History==\nOriginally named Ao Udom became a sanitation (''Sukhaphiban'') on 12 December 1967, which covered parts of subdistricts Thung Sukhla and Surasak, Si Racha district, Chonburi province. Later on 6 October 1970 it was enlarged with subdistrict Nong Kham, Bueng district and area of subdistrict Thung Sukhla. On 24 December 1991 the area has been enlarged again and contains five subdistricts, Surasak, Nong Kham, Bueng, Bo Win and Kha Khan Song.<ref name=\"HISTORY\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/498 |title=History and logo |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> The sanitation changed to subdistrict municipality (''[[Thesaban#Subdistrict-municipality|thesaban tambon]]'') on 24 February 1999, effective on 25 May 1999.<ref>{{cite journal |date=24 February 1999 |title=\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e1a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e19\u0e41\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e10\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e02\u0e32\u0e20\u0e34\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25 \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e55\u0e54\u0e52 |trans-title=Municipal Sanitation Change Act B.E.2542 (1999) |url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2542/A/009/1.PDF |access-date=20 March 2020 |journal=Royal Thai Government Gazette |volume=116 |issue=9 Kor |pages=1-4 |postscript=, effective 25 May 1999}}</ref> The name changed to ''Chaophraya Surasak subdistrict municipality'' on 22 July 2002.<ref>{{cite journal |date=22 July 2002 |title=\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e24\u0e29\u0e0e\u0e35\u0e01\u0e32\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e15\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e48\u0e32\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e38\u0e14\u0e21 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e15\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e25\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e55\u0e54\u0e55 |trans-title=Royal Decree: Change the name of Ao Udom subdistrict municipality to be Chaophraya Surasak subdistrict municipality B.E. 2545 (2002) |url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/00089050.PDF |access-date=20 March 2020 |journal=Royal Thai Government Gazette |volume=119 |issue=68 Kor |pages=17-18}}</ref> The status was upgraded to ''Chaophraya Surasak city municipality'' on 25 July 2013, while the total area was reduced from 306.44 sq.km to 276.99 km<sup>2</sup>.<ref>{{cite journal |date=25 July 2013 |title=\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e01\u0e32\u0e28\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e23\u0e27\u0e07\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e14\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22 \u0e40\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e19\u0e41\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e10\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e15\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e25\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c \u0e2d\u0e33\u0e40\u0e20\u0e2d\u0e28\u0e23\u0e35\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e32 \u0e08\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e31\u0e14\u0e0a\u0e25\u0e1a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e35 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e19\u0e04\u0e23\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c |trans-title=Notification of the Ministry of Interior Re: Change status of Chao Phraya Surasak subdistrict municipality, Si Racha district, Chonburi province is Chao Phraya Surasak city municipality |url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2556/E/088/28.PDF|access-date=10 March 2020 |journal=Royal Thai Government Gazette |volume=130 |issue=88 Ngor |pages=28}}</ref>\n\n==Administration==\n{| class=\"wikitable floatright\"\n! Subdistrict\n! Villages\n! Community\n! People\n! Households\n|-\n| Surasak\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 17\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 63,227\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 44,216\n|-\n| Bueng\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 30,227\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 20,543\n|-\n| Nong Kham\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 30,120\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 19,607\n|-\n| Bo Win\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 15,830\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 12,670\n|-\n| Khao Khan Song\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 3,568\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,926\n|-\n|}\nThe administration of Chaophraya Surasak city municipality is responsible for an area that covers 276.98 square kilometers and consists of five subdistricts, 30 villages (''[[muban]]''), 46 communities (''chumchon''),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/501 |title=Community information |date=2020 |department=City Chao phraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> 143,024 people in 98,962 households.<ref name=\"TDD\"/>\n{{clear}}\n\n==Religion==\nAs of 2019 95% of the population in Chaophraya Surasak city municipality self-identified as ''[[Buddhism|Buddhists]]'' of the [[Theravada#Thailand and Cambodia|Theravada Buddhism]]. There are 32 temples (''[[wat]]'') and seven \"samnak song\", temples who are not official registered. ''[[Muslims]]'' comprising 2% of the population with three [[mosque]]s. ''[[Christians]]'' represent also 2% of the population with three [[Church (building)|churches]]. The remaining 1% of the population are followers of other religions.<ref name=\"SOCIAL\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/556 |title=Social characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Logo==\nThe city logo shows a freight train, which symbolizes industry, buildings that characterize urbanization, pineapples are a reference to agriculture and the mountains in the background pointing to the Khao Khiao mountain range.<ref name=\"HISTORY\"/>\n\n==Infrastructure==\n===Education===\nThere are eight early childhood (Kindergarten) schools and 20 schools for basic education: 10 schools with  primary 1 to secondary 3 level and 10 schools with primary 1 to secondary 6 level. The city has no vocational or tertiary education.<ref name=\"SOCIAL\"/>\n\n===Health===\nThere are eight health promoting hospitals; 1 Surasak, 2 Bueng, 2 Nong Kham, 1 Bo Win, 2 Khao Khan Song.<br>\nFurther Khao Khan Song has one health center (Chaloem Phra Kiat).<ref name=\"SOCIAL\" />\n\n===Transportation===\n[[File:Nong Kham Interchange.png|thumb|Nong Kham Interchange]]\nThere are four major roads in the city:<ref name=\"BASIC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/562 |title=Basic structure |date=2020 |department=City Chao phraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Motorway Route 7 (Thailand)|Motorway 7]]&nbsp;&nbsp;Bangkok - Pattaya - Map Ta Phut\n* National highway no.3 (Sukhumvit road)&nbsp; Bangkok - Trat\n* Highway no.331&nbsp; Sattahip (Chonburi province) - Phanom Sarakham (Chachoengsao province)\n* National route no.3241 connects highway no.331 with Sukhumvit road\nNong Kham Interchange in [[Motorway Route 7 (Thailand)|motorway 7]] is part of the objectives to solve traffic jams to and from the [[Laem Chabang#The port|port of Laem Chabang]].<br>In the city, traffic jams will form on most roads due to traveling to and from schools and in the evening due to the number of flea markets on different roads.\n\n===Waterworks===\n\"Si Racha District Waterworks Office\" produced 47,000 cub.m./day tapwater, which is used by 30,100 households or 30% of the total area in the municipality.<br>\n\"Laem Chabang Waterworks Office\" produced 59,140 cub.m/day tapwater, which is used by 36,400 households or 13% of the total area in the municipality.<br>\nThe conclusion is: 33% of the households (32,450) or 57% of the total area in the municipality do not used tapwater.<ref name=\"BASIC\"/>\n\n===Economy===\nThe total area of agricultural land is 76,610 rai (122.6 sq.km), which accounts for about 44% of the total area in the municipality. The farming mostly delivers tapioca, pineapple, dragon fruit.<ref name=\"BASIC\"/> Animal husbandry consists of seven pig farms and 37 chicken farms. Sriracha Tiger Zoo with an area of 40 ha (100 acres) is in Nong Kham subdistrict. Tourism revenue is 110 million Baht/year. The total number of factories is 214, many of which are concentrated in four \"Industrial Estates\":<ref name=\"ECONOMIC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/558 |title=Economoc characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chao phraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Pinthong Industrial Estate 1 - 160 ha (400 acres)\n* Pinthong Industrial Estate 2 - 120 ha (300 acres)\n* Pinthong Industrial Estate 3 - 160 ha (400 acres)\n* Bo Win Industrial Estate - 540 ha (1330 acres)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Notes==\nReports (data) from Thai government are \"not copyrightable\" (Public Domain), Copyright Act 2537 (1994), section 7.\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://chaoprayasurasak.go.th/}}\n\n{{Metropolitan cities of Thailand}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{coord|13|07|28|N|100|59|57|E|region:TH|display=title}}\n{{Most populous cities in Thailand}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Chonburi Province]]\n\n\n{{chonburi-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                           = Chaophraya Surasak\n| official_name                  = City of Chaophraya Surasak<br>{{lang|th|\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e19\u0e04\u0e23\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c}}\n| native_name                    = {{lang|th|\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c}}\n| nickname                       = \n| translit_lang1                 = \n| translit_lang1_type1           = \n| translit_lang1_info1           =  \n| settlement_type                = [[List of municipalities in Thailand|City Municipality]]\n| motto                          =\n| image_skyline                  = \n| imagesize                      =\n| image_caption                  = \n| image_flag                     =\n| image_seal                     = {{#property:p158}}\n| image_shield                   =\n| image_map                      = \n| map_caption                    = \n| mapsize                        = \n| pushpin_map                    = Thailand Bay of Bangkok#Thailand\n| pushpin_label                  = <small>Chaophraya Surasak</small>\n| pushpin_label_position         = right\n| pushpin_map_caption            = Location in [[Bay of Bangkok]]##Location in [[Thailand]]\n| coordinates                    = {{coord|13|07|28|N|100|59|57|E|region:TH|display=inline}}\n| named_for                      = [[Chaophraya Surasakmontri]]\n| subdivision_type               = [[List of sovereign states|Country]] \n| subdivision_name               = [[Thailand]]\n| subdivision_type1              = [[Provinces of Thailand|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1              = [[Chonburi Province|Chonburi]]\n| subdivision_type2              = [[List of districts of Thailand|District]]\n| subdivision_name2              = [[Si Racha District|Si Racha]]\n| leader_title1                  = \n| leader_name1                   = \n| leader_title2                  =\n| leader_name2                   =\n| leader_title3                  =\n| leader_name3                   =\n| established_title              = Sanitation\n| established_date               = 12 December 1967\n| established_title1             = Subdistrict<br>municipality\n| established_date1              = 25 May 1999\n| established_title2             = City<br>municipality\n| established_date2              = 1 May 2013\n| seat_type                      =\n| seat                           =\n| government_footnotes           =\n| government_type                = \n| leader_party                   =\n| leader_title                   = Mayor\n| leader_name                    = Akom Panchalermchai\n| unit_pref                      = Metric\n| area_footnotes                 = \n| area_rank                      = 2nd\n| area_total_km2                 = 276.98\n| area_land_km2                  =\n| area_note                      = \n| elevation_footnotes            =\n| elevation_m                    =\n| population_footnotes           = <ref name=\"TDD\">{{cite web |url=http://stat.bora.dopa.go.th/stat/statnew/statTDD/ |title=\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e16\u0e34\u0e15\u0e34\u0e08\u0e33\u0e19\u0e27\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e01\u0e23\u0e41\u0e25\u0e30\u0e1a\u0e49\u0e32\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e08\u0e33\u0e1b\u0e35 \u0e1e.\u0e28.2562 |date=31 December 2019 |department=Registration Office Department of the Interior, Ministry of the Interior |language=Thai |trans-title=Statistics, population and house statistics for the year 2019 |access-date=10 March 2020 |postscript= , archiving is not necessary because DOPA provides data from 1993 to future years.}}</ref>\n| population_total               = 143,024\n| population_as_of               = 2019\n| population_rank                = 5th\n| population_density_km2         = 516\n| population_demonym             =\n| population_note                =\n| timezone1                      = [[UTC+07:00|ICT]]\n| utc_offset1                    = +7\n| postal_code_type               = [[Postal codes in Thailand|Postcode]]\n| postal_code                    = 20110\n| area_code_type                 = [[Telephone numbers in Thailand|Calling code]]\n| area_code                      = 038\n| website                        = {{URL|www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/}}\n| footnotes                      =\n}}\n\n'''Chaophraya Surasak''' is a city in [[Chonburi Province]], [[Thailand]].  It was established as a sanitary district in 1967. In 1999, all sanitary districts were upgraded to subdistrict municipalities (''[[Thesaban #Subdistrict-municipality|thesaban tambon]]''). In 2013 it was upgraded to a city municipality (''[[Thesaban#City-municipality|thesaban nakhon]]''). As of 2019, it has a population of 143,024.<ref name=\"TDD\"/> The city covers parts of five subdistricts (''[[tambon]]'') of [[Si Racha District]]. The city is named after [[Chaophraya Surasakmontri]].\n\n==Geography==\n===Location===\nChaophraya Surasak city municipality (''[[Thesaban#City-municipality|thesaban nakhon]]'') with a total area of 276.98 sq.km is located on the east coast of [[Gulf of Thailand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/554 |title=Location and physical characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> It is about 40 kilometers from [[Chonburi]] and 120 kilometers from [[Bangkok]]. Chaophraya Surasak borders to the '''north''': subdistricts (''tambon'') Bang Phra and Nong Kham, district (''amphoe'') Si Racha, province Chonburi, '''east''': subdistrict Khlon Kio, district Ban Bueng and subdistricts Khao Khan Song and Bo Win, district Si Racha, province Chonburi, '''south''': subdistrict Takhian Tia, [[Bang Lamung District|district Bang Lamung]], province Chonburi, '''west''': [[Laem Chabang]] city municipality and [[Si Racha]] town municipality (''[[Thesaban#Town-municipality|thesaban mueang]]''), district Si Racha, province Chonburi and the [[Bay of Bangkok]].\n\n===Topography===\nIn the east of the Chaophraya Surasak municipality is the [[Khao Khiao Massif|Khao Khiao]] mountain range. The foothills alternate with plains to the sea.<ref name=\"RESOURCE\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/560 |title=Resource characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Wildlife Sanctuary===\nThere is one wildlife sanctuary in Khao Khan Song subdistrict: [[Khao Khiao - Khao Chomphu Wildlife Sanctuary]], 145 sq.km (56 sq.mi.)\n\n===Climate===\nChaophraya Surasak city has a tropical savanna climate (K\u00f6ppen climate classification category Aw). Winters are dry and warm. Temperatures rise until May. Mansoon season runs from May through October, with heavy rain and somewhat cooler temperatures during the day, althought nights remain warm. Weather station Laem Chabang, climate data from 1981-2010: The maximum temperature is 39.0 \u00b0C (102.2 \u00b0F) in January and the minimum temperature is 14.0 \u00b0C (57.2 \u00b0F) in December. The maximum average temperature is 33.3 \u00b0C (91.9 \u00b0F) in April and the minimum average temperature is 22.0 \u00b0C (71.6 \u00b0F) in December. Annual rainfall is 1,151 millimeter (45.3 inche) and in January was for 24 hour the rainfall 176.5 millimeter (7 inche).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.climate.tmd.go.th/content/file/75 |title=Climatological Data for the Period 1981-2010 |publisher=Thai Meteorological Department |page=20 |access-date=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Water resources===\nThere are three water reservoirs:\n* Huai Nong Kho, capacity 21,400,000 cub.m.\n* Huai Saphan, capacity 7,650,000 cub.m.\n* Huai Nong Klang Dong, capacity 3,840,00 cub.m.\nFurther there is natural stream Huai Lam, consisting of 20 natural places.<ref name=\"RESOURCE\"/>\n\n==History==\nOriginally named Ao Udom became a sanitation (''Sukhaphiban'') on 12 December 1967, which covered parts of subdistricts Thung Sukhla and Surasak, Si Racha district, Chonburi province. Later on 6 October 1970 it was enlarged with subdistrict Nong Kham, Bueng district and area of subdistrict Thung Sukhla. On 24 December 1991 the area has been enlarged again and contains five subdistricts, Surasak, Nong Kham, Bueng, Bo Win and Kha Khan Song.<ref name=\"HISTORY\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/498 |title=History and logo |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> The sanitation changed to subdistrict municipality (''[[Thesaban#Subdistrict-municipality|thesaban tambon]]'') on 24 February 1999, effective on 25 May 1999.<ref>{{cite journal |date=24 February 1999 |title=\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e1a\u0e31\u0e0d\u0e0d\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e19\u0e41\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e10\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30\u0e02\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e02\u0e32\u0e20\u0e34\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25 \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e55\u0e54\u0e52 |trans-title=Municipal Sanitation Change Act B.E.2542 (1999) |url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2542/A/009/1.PDF |access-date=20 March 2020 |journal=Royal Thai Government Gazette |volume=116 |issue=9 Kor |pages=1-4 |postscript=, effective 25 May 1999}}</ref> The name changed to ''Chaophraya Surasak subdistrict municipality'' on 22 July 2002.<ref>{{cite journal |date=22 July 2002 |title=\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e01\u0e24\u0e29\u0e0e\u0e35\u0e01\u0e32\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e19\u0e0a\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e15\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e48\u0e32\u0e27\u0e2d\u0e38\u0e14\u0e21 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e15\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e25\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c \u0e1e.\u0e28. \u0e52\u0e55\u0e54\u0e55 |trans-title=Royal Decree: Change the name of Ao Udom subdistrict municipality to be Chaophraya Surasak subdistrict municipality B.E. 2545 (2002) |url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/00089050.PDF |access-date=20 March 2020 |journal=Royal Thai Government Gazette |volume=119 |issue=68 Kor |pages=17-18}}</ref> The status was upgraded to ''Chaophraya Surasak city municipality'' on 25 July 2013, while the total area was reduced from 306.44 sq.km to 276.99 sq.km.<ref>{{cite journal |date=25 July 2013 |title=\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e01\u0e32\u0e28\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e17\u0e23\u0e27\u0e07\u0e21\u0e2b\u0e32\u0e14\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22 \u0e40\u0e23\u0e37\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e07 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e35\u0e48\u0e22\u0e19\u0e41\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e07\u0e10\u0e32\u0e19\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e15\u0e33\u0e1a\u0e25\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c \u0e2d\u0e33\u0e40\u0e20\u0e2d\u0e28\u0e23\u0e35\u0e23\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e32 \u0e08\u0e31\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e31\u0e14\u0e0a\u0e25\u0e1a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e35 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e25\u0e19\u0e04\u0e23\u0e40\u0e08\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1e\u0e23\u0e30\u0e22\u0e32\u0e2a\u0e38\u0e23\u0e28\u0e31\u0e01\u0e14\u0e34\u0e4c |trans-title=Notification of the Ministry of Interior Re: Change status of Chao Phraya Surasak subdistrict municipality, Si Racha district, Chonburi province is Chao Phraya Surasak city municipality |url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2556/E/088/28.PDF|access-date=10 March 2020 |journal=Royal Thai Government Gazette |volume=130 |issue=88 Ngor |pages=28}}</ref>\n\n==Administration==\n{| class=\"wikitable floatright\"\n! Subdistrict\n! Villages\n! Community\n! People\n! Households\n|-\n| Surasak\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 17\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 63,227\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 44,216\n|-\n| Bueng\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 30,227\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 20,543\n|-\n| Nong Kham\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 30,120\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 19,607\n|-\n| Bo Win\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 15,830\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 12,670\n|-\n| Khao Khan Song\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 3,568\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,926\n|-\n|}\nThe administration of Chaophraya Surasak city municipality is responsible for an area that covers 276.98 square kilometers and consists of five subdistricts, 30 villages (''[[muban]]''), 46 communities (''chumchon''),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/501 |title=Community information |date=2020 |department=City Chao phraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref> 143,024 people in 98,962 households.<ref name=\"TDD\"/>\n{{clear}}\n\n==Religion==\nAs of 2019 95% of the population in Chaophraya Surasak city municipality self-identified as ''[[Buddhism|Buddhists]]'' of the [[Theravada#Thailand and Cambodia|Theravada Buddhism]]. There are 32 temples (''[[wat]]'') and seven \"samnak song\", temples who are not official registered. ''[[Muslims]]'' comprising 2% of the population with three [[mosque]]s. ''[[Christians]]'' represent also 2% of the population with three [[Church (building)|churches]]. The remaining 1% of the population are followers of other religions.<ref name=\"SOCIAL\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/556 |title=Social characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chaophraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Logo==\nThe city logo shows a freight train, which symbolizes industry, buildings that characterize urbanization, pineapples are a reference to agriculture and the mountains in the background pointing to the Khao Khiao mountain range.<ref name=\"HISTORY\"/>\n\n==Infrastructure==\n===Education===\nThere are eight early childhood (Kindergarten) schools and 20 schools for basic education: 10 schools with  primary 1 to secondary 3 level and 10 schools with primary 1 to secondary 6 level. The city has no vocational or tertiary education.<ref name=\"SOCIAL\"/>\n\n===Health===\nThere are eight health promoting hospitals; 1 Surasak, 2 Bueng, 2 Nong Kham, 1 Bo Win, 2 Khao Khan Song.<br>\nFurther Khao Khan Song has one health center (Chaloem Phra Kiat).<ref name=\"SOCIAL/>\n\n===Transportation===\n[[File:Nong Kham Interchange.png|thumb|Nong Kham Interchange]]\nThere are four major roads in the city:<ref name=\"BASIC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/562 |title=Basic structure |date=2020 |department=City Chao phraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Motorway Route 7 (Thailand)|Motorway 7]]&nbsp;&nbsp;Bangkok - Pattaya - Map Ta Phut\n* National highway no.3 (Sukhumvit road)&nbsp; Bangkok - Trat\n* Highway no.331&nbsp; Sattahip (Chonburi province) - Phanom Sarakham (Chachoengsao province)\n* National route no.3241 connects highway no.331 with Sukhumvit road\nNong Kham Interchange in [[Motorway Route 7 (Thailand)|motorway 7]] is part of the objectives to solve traffic jams to and from the [[Laem Chabang#The port|port of Laem Chabang]].<br>In the city, traffic jams will form on most roads due to traveling to and from schools and in the evening due to the number of flea markets on different roads.\n\n===Waterworks===\n\"Si Racha District Waterworks Office\" produced 47,000 cub.m./day tapwater, which is used by 30,100 households or 30% of the total area in the municipality.<br>\n\"Laem Chabang Waterworks Office\" produced 59,140 cub.m/day tapwater, which is used by 36,400 households or 13% of the total area in the municipality.<br>\nThe conclusion is: 33% of the households (32,450) or 57% of the total area in the municipality do not used tapwater.<ref name=\"BASIC\"/>\n\n===Economy===\nThe total area of agricultural land is 76,610 rai (122.6 sq.km), which accounts for about 44% of the total area in the municipality. The farming mostly delivers tapioca, pineapple, dragon fruit.<ref name=\"BASIC\"/> Animal husbandry consists of seven pig farms and 37 chicken farms. Sriracha Tiger Zoo with an area of 40 ha (100 acres) is in Nong Kham subdistrict. Tourism revenue is 110 million Baht/year. The total number of factories is 214, many of which are concentrated in four \"Industrial Estates\":<ref name=\"ECONOMIC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaoprayasurasak.go.th/public/texteditor/data/index/menu/558 |title=Economoc characteristics |date=2020 |department=City Chao phraya Surasak |website=chaoprayasurasak.go.th |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Pinthong Industrial Estate 1 - 160 ha (400 acres)\n* Pinthong Industrial Estate 2 - 120 ha (300 acres)\n* Pinthong Industrial Estate 3 - 160 ha (400 acres)\n* Bo Win Industrial Estate - 540 ha (1330 acres)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Notes==\nReports (data) from Thai government are \"not copyrightable\" (Public Domain), Copyright Act 2537 (1994), section 7.\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://chaoprayasurasak.go.th/}}\n\n{{Metropolitan cities of Thailand}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{coord|13|07|28|N|100|59|57|E|region:TH|display=title}}\n{{Most populous cities in Thailand}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Chonburi Province]]\n\n\n{{chonburi-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 -WP:WCWproject (Unbalanced quotes in ref name or illegal character. - Spelling and typography)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chaophraya_Surasak"}
